truction and meliorism. At the same time, Stroud is careful to point out the ways that Ambedkar pushed back against Dewey’s paradigm and developed his own approach to challenges in India. The result is a nuanced study of one of the most important figures in Indian history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPragmatism. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aJohn Dewey, Bhimrao Ambedkar, pragmatism, caste, rhetoric, Buddhism, rhetorical theory, philosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023 Englishz978311131916208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023z9783111318240oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107665090 cprintz978022682388140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226823898423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226823898/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-131916-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023